CLARK vs. MAYOR AND COMMON COUNCIL (West Bay City), No. 15983; 4 D. L. N., 8; 70 N. W., 581.

(Certiorari to Bay.)

To compel respondent to enter into a contract with relator for city printing, for which bids had been requested and received ; it appearing that the contract had already been let to another party and the work partly performed.

The circuit judge granted the writ. Reversed and order vacated, with costs of both courts, April 6, 1897.
